pageContext.claim: “Mexico must apprehend all illegals and not let them make the long march up to the United States, or we will have no other choice than to Close the Border and/or institute Tariffs. Our Country is FULL!”
pageContext.analysis: The country is not full. Mexico routinely detains Central American migrants and has deported more than 2 million since 2001. The Trump administration has negotiated a new trade agreement with Mexico that would not leave much room for tariffs if it's ratified, as Trump wants.
